Nomad's chronicles - part 3
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
The discovery changed the way we had comprehended the world.
Void of any special powers, the monolith gifted its observers with inspiration of unknown strength.
New, daring ideas were shaped in our minds. New ways to see and understand things. Visions.


Some feared it.
Called them unnatural.
The monolith became subject of heated debates.


Supporters and opponents had kept the balance until the first death occurred.